# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# multi-model-flow configuration
#
# Copy the bits you need into your shell profile (~/.zshrc, ~/.bashrc) or export
# them before launching Claude Code. These are read by the bundled `ollama-local`
# MCP server. (This file is a template — it is NOT loaded automatically.)
#
# WHERE EACH MODEL IN THE WORKFLOW IS SET
#   • Claude tiers (Planner / Worker-adapt / Reviewer) → edit the `model:` field
#     in agents/planner.md, agents/worker.md, agents/reviewer.md.
#         planner.md  → model: opus     (planning)
#         worker.md   → model: haiku     (adapts drafts, writes files)
#         reviewer.md → model: sonnet    (review; escalates to opus)
#     Use tier aliases (opus/sonnet/haiku/fable) or pinned IDs (claude-opus-4-8).
#   • Worker-generation backend (the local-LLM role) → the env vars below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Ollama backend (default) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Endpoint for the local Ollama server.
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# Optional: pin the Ollama model. Unset → the skill auto-selects the best
# installed coding model (or first installed). No model name is hardcoded.
OLLAMA_DEFAULT_MODEL=
# Generation timeout in seconds (default 1500 = 25 min).
OLLAMA_TIMEOUT=1500

# ── OpenRouter backend (used only with the [openrouter] flag) ────────────────
# Get a key at https://openrouter.ai/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# The model to generate with, e.g. qwen/qwen-2.5-coder-32b-instruct
# (override per-run with [model:<id>]).
#   • Paid/credit keys can use any model, incl. the auto-router: openrouter/auto
#   • Free-tier or model-restricted keys must use a ":free" model id
#     (e.g. cohere/north-mini-code:free) — openrouter/auto returns HTTP 404
#     "no models match your request and model restrictions" on a restricted key.
OPENROUTER_MODEL=
# Endpoint (rarely changed).
OPENROUTER_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
